rd hours, using the standard labour rate.\",11\n951,\"\"\"LABOUR RATE VARIANCE\"\"\",\"Labour rate variance is a financial metric used to measure the difference between the actual hourly wage rate paid and the standard rate expected to be paid, multiplied by the actual hours worked. It is calculated by comparing the actual hours paid at the actual rate with the actual hours paid at the standard rate. This can be expressed mathematically as (Standard Rate - Actual Rate) * Actual Hours paid. Essentially, it evaluates the effect of the actual labor rate differing from the standard labor rate, using the actual hours worked. The quiz on labour rate variance involves calculating this variance given budgeted and actual labour costs and hours.\",6\n1019,\"\"\"OPERATIONAL EFFICIENCY VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Operational efficiency variance\"\" is calculated by comparing the actual hours worked with the revised standard hours for actual output, multiplied by the standard rate per hour. This metric measures the difference in hours between actual performance and revised standards, indicating how efficiently labor was used. It is measured in hours.\",3\n1020,\"\"\"QUIZ: LABOUR EFFICIENCY VARIANCES AND OPERATIONAL VARIANCES\"\"\",\"\"\"This quiz involves calculating traditional labour efficiency variance, planning efficiency variance, and operational efficiency variance for a new product, and commenting on how the operational efficiency variance provides a more appropriate indication of the factory manager's performance.\"\"\",3\n1018,\"\"\"PLANNING EFFICIENCY VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Planning efficiency variance is calculated by comparing the original standard hours for actual output with the revised standard hours for actual output, multiplied by the standard rate per hour.\"\"\",2\n1034,\"\"\"STANDARD LABOUR COST\"\"\",\"The \"\"STANDARD LABOUR COST\"\" was calculated as 2 hours of labor at a rate of $10 per hour.\",2\n1822,\"\"\"PRODUCTION DIRECTOR PERFORMANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"The performa